{"name":"Perform [Specialization]","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"perk","data":{"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Perform: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">You know how to put on a show.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Specialization: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">When you gain this perk, choose a musical instrument or other performance art, such as flute, horn, singing, or interpretive dance. You can gain this perk multiple times with different specializations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Benefit:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> You gain the normal perk bonuses to checks related to your performance, such as composition, showmanship, and finding gigs.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Examples:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> drum, dwarven opera, epic poetry, fiddle, goblin nose flute, harp, horn, interpretive dance, juggling, kazoo, lute, lyre, motivational speaking, oratory, orc masked theater, piano, singing, tambourine, troll throat-singing.</span></p>","name":"","total":0,"abil":"cha","mod":0,"encumbered":false,"feat":0,"itemb":0,"misc":0,"abilities":{"str":{"label":"STR","value":"str"},"con":{"label":"CON","value":"con"},"dex":{"label":"DEX","value":"dex"},"int":{"label":"INT","value":"int"},"wis":{"label":"WIS","value":"wis"},"cha":{"label":"CHA","value":"cha"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1kq781G8zZmU4Ads"}
{"name":"Contacts [Specialization]","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"perk","data":{"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Contacts: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">You know a guy who knows a guy.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Specialization: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">When you gain this perk, choose a geographical location, up to the size of a country, where you know people who owe you favors. You can gain this perk multiple times with different areas, and the areas may overlap as long as they are not completely identical.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Benefit:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> You gain the normal perk bonuses to Society checks made to gather information in the area you chose for this perk. Also, you can gather information without being physically present, as long as you have a way of communicating with your contacts, and enough time for them to reply.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Acquisitions:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> Once per adventure, while in the area you chose, you can call upon your contacts to provide you with equipment worth up to 100 gp. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Refuge:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> Once per adventure, while in the area you chose, you can call upon your contacts to provide you with a safe place to stay for up to a week. As long as you do not leave this refuge, the Difficulty for Society checks and other mundane attempts to find you increases by +5.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Transportation:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> Once per adventure, you may call upon your contacts to get you into or out of the area you chose for this perk without being detected. You must be able to communicate with your contacts in order to receive their help getting into the area, and the exact method by which they transport you is up to the GM.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Costly Favors: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">At the GM&rsquo;s discretion, you may be able to call on your contacts for favors beyond those listed under Acquisitions, Refuge, and Transportation, but this may exhaust your contacts, causing you to lose this perk permanently.</span></p>","name":"","total":0,"abil":"cha","mod":0,"encumbered":false,"feat":0,"itemb":0,"misc":0,"abilities":{"str":{"label":"STR","value":"str"},"con":{"label":"CON","value":"con"},"dex":{"label":"DEX","value":"dex"},"int":{"label":"INT","value":"int"},"wis":{"label":"WIS","value":"wis"},"cha":{"label":"CHA","value":"cha"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6DHhVcEVJVjgW4ZX"}
{"name":"Esoteric Knowledge [Specialization]","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"perk","data":{"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Esoteric Knowledge: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">You know a lot about a specialized subject.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Specialization: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">When you gain this perk, choose a subject that you know a great deal about, such as economics, geography, or mathematics. The subject you choose should not be identical to the Arcana, Engineering, History, Nature, Religion, Society, or Warfare skills, but it can be a subset of those skills, such as art history or clockmaking. You can gain this perk multiple times with different specializations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Benefit:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> You gain the normal perk bonuses to checks related to the subject you chose. This includes research in that subject, writing about that subject, and teaching that subject.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Examples:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> Art history, astronomy, biology, chemistry, clockmaking, cryptography, economics, geography, literature, mathematics, physics, political science, psychology, theater.</span></p>","name":"","total":0,"abil":"int","mod":0,"encumbered":false,"feat":0,"itemb":0,"misc":0,"abilities":{"str":{"label":"STR","value":"str"},"con":{"label":"CON","value":"con"},"dex":{"label":"DEX","value":"dex"},"int":{"label":"INT","value":"int"},"wis":{"label":"WIS","value":"wis"},"cha":{"label":"CHA","value":"cha"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BpumcsGXIb3g5GLQ"}
{"name":"Profession [Specialization]","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"perk","data":{"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Profession: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">You know how to do a job and do it well.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Specialization: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">When you gain this perk, choose a job that you know how to do, such as farmer, sailor, or wagoneer. You can gain this perk multiple times with different specializations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Benefit:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> You gain the normal perk bonuses to checks related to the profession you selected. This includes assessing the skill of other workers, advertising your services, and running a business.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Day Job: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">When you have downtime, you can practice your profession in order to make small amounts of money. Make an appropriate ability check, with the perk bonus applied. After deducting living expenses, you earn gp equal to your check result in profit or wages every month.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Compare with Craft:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> If a job involves making a physical object, Craft is usually more appropriate. If it involves providing a service or creating something intangible, use Profession instead.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span class=\"RPGMaterial\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Examples:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> academic, bartender, coachman, farmer, ferryman, lawyer, merchant, novelist, sailor, tinker.</span></p>","name":"","total":0,"abil":"wis","mod":0,"encumbered":false,"feat":0,"itemb":0,"misc":0,"abilities":{"str":{"label":"STR","value":"str"},"con":{"label":"CON","value":"con"},"dex":{"label":"DEX","value":"dex"},"int":{"label":"INT","value":"int"},"wis":{"label":"WIS","value":"wis"},"cha":{"label":"CHA","value":"cha"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CtKf85mRwi2XAwYW"}
{"name":"Craft [Specialization]","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"perk","data":{"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Craft: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">You know how to make things.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Specialization: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">When you gain this perk, choose a craft that you have mastered, such as blacksmithing, leatherworking, or sculpture. You can gain this perk multiple times with different specializations.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Benefit:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> You gain the normal perk bonuses to checks related to the craft you selected. This includes appraising the quality of goods, identifying the maker of goods, or attempting to repair goods.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Crafting:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> You can create mundane goods related to your craft. Creating goods costs half as much as buying the goods, and requires 6 hours of work for every 25 gp that the goods would normally cost to buy. You may only spend up to 12 hours working between long rests.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Compare with Profession:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> If a job involves making a physical object, Craft is usually more appropriate. If it involves providing a service or creating something intangible, use Profession instead.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in right 3.75in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Examples:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> Blacksmithing, bookbinding, calligraphy, distilling, jewelcutting, leatherworking, portraiture, sculpture, tailoring, woodcarving.</span></p>","name":"","total":0,"abil":"wis","mod":0,"encumbered":false,"feat":0,"itemb":0,"misc":0,"abilities":{"str":{"label":"STR","value":"str"},"con":{"label":"CON","value":"con"},"dex":{"label":"DEX","value":"dex"},"int":{"label":"INT","value":"int"},"wis":{"label":"WIS","value":"wis"},"cha":{"label":"CHA","value":"cha"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WmV0lO6svE3CWGAa"}
{"name":"Language [Specialization]","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"perk","data":{"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Language: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">You know an exotic language.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Specialization: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">When you gain this perk, choose a mundane language. If you are trained in Arcana, you may choose a supernatural language instead, and if you are trained in History, you may choose an ancient language. You can gain this perk multiple times with different languages.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Benefit: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">You learn to speak, read, and write the language you chose. If you are illiterate in a language, you may take this perk to become literate in that language. This perk does not provide a bonus to any ability or skill checks.</span></p>","name":"","total":0,"abil":"cha","mod":0,"encumbered":false,"feat":0,"itemb":0,"misc":0,"abilities":{"str":{"label":"STR","value":"str"},"con":{"label":"CON","value":"con"},"dex":{"label":"DEX","value":"dex"},"int":{"label":"INT","value":"int"},"wis":{"label":"WIS","value":"wis"},"cha":{"label":"CHA","value":"cha"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"eKBb41PaevVn160w"}
{"name":"Heroic Reputation [Specialization]","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"perk","data":{"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Heroic Reputation: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Certain people know you to be honest and capable, and to share their agenda.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Specialization: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">When you gain this perk, choose a group of people, such as &ldquo;citizens of the town of Haymarket&rdquo; or &ldquo;worshippers of Deus Valiant.&rdquo; If the group consists of all the people in a geographical location, the location should not be larger than a mid-sized town and its immediate surroundings. You can gain this perk multiple times with different groups.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Benefit:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> You gain the normal perk bonuses to Deception and Persuasion checks, as well as Charisma checks, involving people in the chosen group. You also gain these bonuses to Intimidate checks against enemies of the chosen group.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Draw a Crowd: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">If you publicly announce your presence in a place where you could reasonably expect to find a member of the chosen group, at least 1d10 members of the group make themselves known to you within 1 hour.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">The Costs of Fame: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">If you betray the trust of the chosen group repeatedly, or in a significant way, the GM may decide that it ruins your reputation, and you permanently lose this perk. You cannot take this perk again with the same group after losing it in this manner.</span></p>","name":"","total":0,"abil":"cha","mod":0,"encumbered":false,"feat":0,"itemb":0,"misc":0,"abilities":{"str":{"label":"STR","value":"str"},"con":{"label":"CON","value":"con"},"dex":{"label":"DEX","value":"dex"},"int":{"label":"INT","value":"int"},"wis":{"label":"WIS","value":"wis"},"cha":{"label":"CHA","value":"cha"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"h8Oqs5rhHZDdgFpr"}
{"_id":"l1vI1BngXz56Cw6d","name":"Lifestyle","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"perk","data":{"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Lifestyle: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">You know how to find the little things that make life worthwhile.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Benefit: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">During every adventure, you can acquire up to 10gp of food, drink, clothing, lodging, or transportation for free. This can represent a passive income stream that you use to support your lifestyle, an expertise in negotiating with innkeepers, or a title that makes suppliers eager to please, among other things.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Extravagance: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">You can take this perk multiple times, and for each additional instance you have, your budget doubles (the second <em>lifestyle</em> perk gives you 20gp, the third 40gp, etc.).</span></p>","name":"","total":0,"abil":"cha","mod":0,"encumbered":false,"feat":0,"itemb":0,"misc":0,"abilities":{"str":{"label":"STR","value":"str"},"con":{"label":"CON","value":"con"},"dex":{"label":"DEX","value":"dex"},"int":{"label":"INT","value":"int"},"wis":{"label":"WIS","value":"wis"},"cha":{"label":"CHA","value":"cha"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Public Feud [Specialization]","permission":{"default":0,"hsFJxrWN4M5Ezw3L":3},"type":"perk","data":{"description":"<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Public Feud: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">People know who your enemies are, and you can find like-minded individuals on the basis of your mutual foe.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Specialization: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">When you gain this perk, choose a group of people, such as &ldquo;the corsairs of Nintar&rdquo; or &ldquo;cultists of the Dragon of Night.&rdquo; If the group consists of all the people in a geographical location, the location should not be larger than a mid-sized town and its immediate surroundings. You can gain this perk multiple times with different groups.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Benefit:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"> You gain the normal perk bonuses to Deception and Persuasion checks, as well as Charisma checks, involving people who oppose the chosen group. You also gain these bonuses to Intimidate checks against members of the chosen group.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">Draw a Mob: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">If you publicly announce your presence in a place where you could reasonably expect to find enemies of the chosen group, at least 1d10 individuals who are also opposed to the group make themselves known to you within 1 hour. <strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .25in; border: none; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext 1.5pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">~<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">The Costs of Fame: </span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt;\">If you flee or otherwise fail to oppose the chosen group once you make your presence known, the GM may decide that it ruins your reputation, and you permanently lose this perk. You cannot take this perk again with the same group after losing it in this manner.</span></p>","name":"","total":0,"abil":"cha","mod":0,"encumbered":false,"feat":0,"itemb":0,"misc":0,"abilities":{"str":{"label":"STR","value":"str"},"con":{"label":"CON","value":"con"},"dex":{"label":"DEX","value":"dex"},"int":{"label":"INT","value":"int"},"wis":{"label":"WIS","value":"wis"},"cha":{"label":"CHA","value":"cha"}}},"flags":[],"img":"icons/svg/book.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zomb9hTHHi2mwpia"}
